ofessor%20and%20geneticist%20Yousin%20Suh%2C%20lead%20author%20of%20the%20new%20study%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BSince%20aging%20occurs%20in%20the%20ovaries%20so%20much%20more%20rapidly%2C%20why%20don't%20we%20use%20ovaries%20as%20a%20very%20fast%20test%20platform%20for%20geroprotectors%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221c0fcbac-df77-428f-b536-f032e6647bb3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20ovary%20could%20be%20a%20perfect%20testing%20ground%20for%20slowing%20down%20aging%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22918%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22suh%20lab%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673fd3129f2901eb603646af%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22786%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGeneticist%20Yousin%20Suh%20studies%20ovarian%20aging.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Yousin%20Suh%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20longevity%20scientists%20have%20known%20that%20the%20ovary%20is%20the%20fastest-aging%20organ%20in%20the%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuh's%20new%20study%20goes%20deeper.%20It%20shows%20that%20ovarian%20aging%20is%20a%20great%20proxy%20for%20overall%20human%20aging%20at%20a%20molecular%20level%20%E2%80%94%20ovarian%20aging%20is%20just%20happening%20several%20decades%20earlier%2C%20and%20very%20rapidly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20first%20time%20where%20you've%20seen%20a%20really%20solid%20study%20done%20by%20a%20leading%20aging%20researcher%20that%20is%20demonstrating%20that%20a%20very%20highly%20conserved%20pathway%20that%20drives%20aging%20is%20happening%20in%20the%20ovary%2C%26quot%3B%20Francesca%20Duncan%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20reproductive%20science%20at%20Northwestern%20University%2C%20told%20BI.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuncan%20said%20for%20many%20years%2C%20aging%20researchers%20were%20hesitant%20to%20consider%20ovarian%20changes%20as%20a%20true%20aging%20phenomenon%20because%20they%20happen%20when%20women%20are%20still%20relatively%20young.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20just%20don't%20consider%20women%20in%20their%2030s%20to%2050s%20in%20that%20'old'%20category%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20think%20that%20tide%20has%20turned%20because%20we%20know%20this%20is%20an%20aging%20process%20and%20it%20has%20significant%20clinical%20and%20societal%20implications.%20So%20more%20and%20more%20people%20are%20paying%20attention%20to%20this%20concept%20of%20ovarian%20aging%20and%20considering%20it%20as%20a%20true%20aging%20process.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20study%2C%20Suh's%20team%20evaluated%20human%20ovary%20tissue%20samples%20from%20four%20young%20women%20(aged%2023-29)%20and%20four%20more%20%26quot%3Breproductively%20aged%26quot%3B%20women%20(49-54)%20to%20create%20an%20%26quot%3Batlas%26quot%3B%20of%20aging%20across%20every%20cell%20type%20in%20the%20ovary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20study%20displays%20in%20fine%20cellular%20and%20molecular%20detail%20how%20human%20ovaries%20age%2C%20and%20how%20genetics%20impact%20the%20process.%20It%20shows%20that%20one%20of%20the%20critical%20hallmarks%20of%20aging%2C%20mTOR%20signaling%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bscreaming%20high%26quot%3B%20in%20middle-aged%20women's%20ovaries%20across%20all%20cell%20types%2C%20Suh%20said.%20That%20suggests%20those%2050-year-old%20ovaries%20could%20be%20a%20great%20model%20for%20studying%20aging%20and%20for%20rapidly%20testing%20out%20drugs%20that%20scientists%20think%20might%20extend%20human%20lifespan%20and%20healthspan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20just%20do%20not%20get%20the%20message%2C%26quot%3B%20Suh%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20think%2C%20'oh%2C%20who%20wants%20a%20baby%20until%20you're%2060%3F%20Or%2C%20who%20wants%20a%20period%20until%20you're%2060%20or%2070%3F'%20That's%20not%20the%20point.%20The%20point%20is%20we%20want%20them%20to%20%3Cem%3Eslow%20down%20aging%3C%2Fem%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChanges%20in%20ovarian%20aging%20are%20also%20rapid%2C%20specific%2C%20and%20traceable%20with%20widely%20available%20tools%2C%20such%20as%20the%20common%20blood%20tests%20that%20measure%20a%20woman's%20ovarian%20reserve%20or%20inflammatory%20markers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20something%20works%20in%20the%20ovary%20in%20terms%20of%20delaying%20aging%2C%20chances%20are%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20geroprotector%20of%20the%20whole%20body%2C%26quot%3B%20Suh%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20reproduction%3B%20the%20ovary%20does%20coordinate%20and%20orchestrate%20health.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Duncan%20cautioned%20that%20while%20the%20idea%20of%20using%20ovaries%20as%20a%20proxy%20for%20whole-body%20aging%20is%20%26quot%3Btantalizing%2C%26quot%3B%20more%20research%20will%20still%20be%20needed%20to%20confirm%20the%20technique.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20needs%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20more%20studies%20of%3A%20how%20do%20those%20changes%20that%20are%20happening%20in%20the%20ovary%2C%20how%20do%20those%20directly%20translate%20into%20changes%20into%20overall%20health%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e0739a16-2421-4785-8e34-c4a220ad66bf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHot%20antiaging%20supplements%20and%20drugs%2C%20like%20metformin%20and%20NMN%2C%20could%20be%20tested%20faster%20on%20ovaries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22metformin%20pills%20spilling%20out%20of%20a%20bottle%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63ebe30765b555001890753d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222343%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECorbis%20News%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20date%2C%20there%20are%20no%20drugs%20approved%20in%20the%20US%20to%20treat%20aging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20there's%20a%20patchwork%20of%20influencers%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-a-longevity-clinic-executive-physical-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclinics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20high-end%20spas%20all%