onia%26quot%3B%2C%20a%20term%20that%20healthcare%20providers%20use%20to%20refer%20to%20an%20illness%20that%20is%20less%20severe%20than%20full-blown%20pneumonia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBed%20rest%20or%20hospitalization%20are%20usually%20not%20needed%2C%20which%20is%20why%20it%20was%20nicknamed%20%26quot%3Bwalking%20pneumonia%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Causes%20Walking%20Pneumonia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWalking%20pneumonia%20is%20usually%20caused%20by%20a%20common%20bacterium%20called%20Mycoplasma%20pneumonia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInfections%20caused%20by%20this%20bacteria%20are%20generally%20mild%20but%20can%20be%20severe%20in%20some%20cases.%20It%20is%20often%20diagnosed%20by%20a%20physical%20exam%20or%20an%20X-ray.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ESymptoms%20Of%20Walking%20Pneumonia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWalking%20pneumonia%20has%20flu-like%20symptoms%2C%20including%20fever%2C%20sore%20throat%20and%20cough.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20person%20with%20walking%20pneumonia%20also%20has%20some%20mild%20breathing%20difficulties%20that%20last%20longer%20than%20the%20standard%20three%20to%20five%20days%20of%20an%20acute%20respiratory%20infection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Walking%20Pneumonia%20Spreads%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWalking%20pneumonia%20can%20spread%20when%20an%20infected%20person%20coughs%20or%20sneezes%2C%20and%20someone%20else%20breathes%20in%20those%20respiratory%20droplets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20occurs%20most%20often%20in%20crowded%20settings%2C%20including%20schools%20and%20colleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EDelhi%20Continues%20To%20Breathe%20Toxic%20Air%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdelhi-continues-to-breathe-toxic-air-aqi-at-371-trains-delayed-7076596%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDelhi%3C%2Fa%3E%20today%20woke%20up%20to%20another%20polluted%20morning%20with%20a%20thin%20layer%20of%20haze%20and%20smog%