tories%3A%20report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22OpenAI%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673feb20fa0140cdd564d117%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpenAI%20has%20already%20positioned%20itself%20as%20a%20rival%20to%20Google%20Search%20with%20the%20recent%20launch%20of%20ChatGPT%20search.%3Cp%3ENurPhoto%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOpenAI%20is%20considering%20making%20a%20web%20browser%2C%20sources%20told%20The%20Information.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20browser%20would%20be%20integrated%20with%20ChatGPT%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGoogle%20is%20doubling%20down%20on%20AI%20for%20search%2C%20too%2C%20starting%20on%20mobile.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-of-openai-company-chatgpt-elon-musk-founded-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20eyeing%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etwo%20territories%20that%20have%20long%20been%20dominated%20by%20Google%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D1a78e601d387fbc0b4f03781af5a45d016543f9aa4ff7afcfa8a0e7ead4b3079%26postID%3D673fd17bcb042e5dec1400fc%26postSlug%3Dopenai-google-search-engine-chrome-web-browser-competition-2024-11%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.theinformation.com%252Farticles%252Fopenai-considers-taking-on-google-with-browser%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Information%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20web%20browsing%20and%20search.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AI%20startup%20is%20at%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20considering%20the%20development%20of%20a%20web%20browser%20that%20would%20be%20integrated%20with%20OpenAI's%20ChatGPT%2C%20sources%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter%20told%20The%20Information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20has%20also%20approached%20travel%2C%20retail%2C%20real%20estate%2C%20and%20food%20websites%20about%20a%20search%20tool%20that%20would%20allow%20visitors%20to%20interact%20with%20their%20sites%20in%20the%20same%20conversational%20way%20a%20user%20might%20interact%20with%20ChatGPT%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Thursday%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20source%20who%20has%20seen%20the%20prototype%20of%20the%20tool%20told%20The%20Information%20that%20the%20new%20product%20is%20called%20NLWeb%2C%20or%20Natural%20Language%20Web.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpokespeople%20for%20Google%20and%20OpenAI%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeveloping%20a%20web%20browser%20and%20a%20search%20tool%20would%20be%20a%20bold%20step%20into%20two%20fields%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20%E2%80%94%20for%20now%20%E2%80%94%20a%20comfortable%20market%20dominance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20August%2C%20Google%20Chrome%20held%20about%2065%25%20of%20the%20global%20web%20browser%20market%20share%2C%20according%20to%20Statista%2C%20a%20data%20analytics%20firm.%20And%20as%20of%20January%2C%20Google%20Search%20accounted%20for%20about%2082%25%20of%20the%20global%20search%20engine%20market%20share.%20Search%20is%20a%20big%20business%20for%20Google%2C%20generating%20%2449.4%20billion%20in%20the%20three%20months%20ending%20September%2030%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20half%20of%20the%20company's%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20is%20also%20doubling%20down%20on%20AI%20for%20search.%20The%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-search-lens-ai-gemini-overviews-new-features-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20last%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20was%20rolling%20out%20a%20series%20of%20changes%20to%20Search%2C%20starting%20on%20mobile.%20An%20entirely%20new%20Search%20experience%20uses%20AI%20to%20organize%20the%20page's%20layout%2C%20grouping%20results%20into%20different%20categories%20and%20pushing%20videos%2C%20forum%20links%2C%20and%20other%20widgets%20to%20the%20top%20of%20the%20page.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultiple%20sources%20told%20The%20Information%20that%20OpenAI%20was%20nowhere%20close%20to%20launching%20a%20browser.%20But%20in%20a%20sign%20of%20the%20company's%20interest%20in%20exploring%20such%20a%20product%2C%20OpenAI%20hired%20two%20key%20developers%20of%20Google%20Chrome%20this%20year%2C%20including%20Ben%20Goodger%2C%20a%20founding%20member%20of%20the%20Chrome%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20already%20has%20positioned%20ChatGPT%20as%20a%20search%20engine%20rival%20with%20the%20release%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-steps-up-google-challenge-launches-chatgpt-search-tool-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%20search%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20October.%20The%20feature%20allows%20the%20chatbot%20to%20provide%20real-time%20answers%20on%20areas%20like%20the%20weather%20or%20the%20stock%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20dominance%20in%20search%20and%20web%20browsing%20is%20indisputable%2C%20but%20that%20may%20come%20under%20threat%20with%20the%20Justice%20Department's%20request%20this%20week%20to%20force%20a%20sale%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-sell-chrome-search-winners-losers-doj-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChrome.%20%3C%2Fa%3EIn%20August%2C%20a%20judge%20ruled%20that%20Google%20maintains%20an%20illegal%20monopoly%20of%20the%20advertising%20and%20search%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20said%20it%20would%20appeal%20any%20ruling%20on%20the%20case%20and%20that%20the%20DOJ%20is%20pushing%20a%20%26quot%3Bradical%20agenda.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-google-search-engine-chrome-web-browser-competition-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%